_pdbx_entry_details.nonpolymer_details       
;THE AUTHORS STATE THAT SOME BETA LACTAM ANTIBIOTICS, SUCH AS FAROPENEM, CAN BE PROCESSED OR DEGRADED AFTER ACYLATION OF L,D-TRANSPEPTIDASES. THIS ENTRY PRESENT AS A SIMILAR CASE WITH LDTMT1 AND LDTMT2, BUT IN THIS CASE FAROPENEM WAS PROCESSED UNTIL AN ACETYL FRAGMENT THAT REMAINED COVALENTLY LINKED AT CATALYTIC CYSTEINE.
;
